cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper utilizes hyperspectral imaging technology and transfer learning to establish a model for identifying maize seeds. Computer vision techniques are used to process the spectral images and the VGG-19 network, which is a popular deep learning architecture for image recognition, is used as the backbone of the model. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses transfer learning, a popular machine learning technique, to improve the accuracy of the model with limited data samples. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the retrieval of information from hyperspectral images of maize seeds to identify their cultivars. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to establish a model for identifying maize seeds, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses a neural network architecture (VGG-19) as the backbone of the model for identifying maize seeds.
